%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 5e28c2e20bb6c4240a55d8edffb777ec, type: 3}
  m_Name: ReedGraveyard
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NewDialogueData
  npcName: Reed
  dialogueLines:
  - LineID: Start
    Speaker: Reed
    text: Hey Echo! Long time no see Just paying my usual visit to Darry.  Everything's
      still vivid in my head, how that night went...do you have some time right now?
    lineTone: 0
    NPCGender: male
    NextLineID: 
    endDialogueAfterLine: 0
    choices:
    - text: Sure.
      NextLineID: Nice
      moralityChange: 1
      direction: 0
      objectiveToActivate: 
    - text: Not really, but go ahead
      NextLineID: Mean
      moralityChange: -1
      direction: 1
      objectiveToActivate: 
    - text: I mean, might be awkward, but why not?
      NextLineID: Nice
      moralityChange: 1
      direction: 2
      objectiveToActivate: 
    - text: I need to go walk my hamster...
      NextLineID: Mean
      moralityChange: -1
      direction: 3
      objectiveToActivate: 
    objectivesToActivate: []
  - LineID: Nice
    Speaker: Reed
    text: Thanks, I've been really needing to vent.
    lineTone: 1
    NPCGender: male
    NextLineID: Part I
    endDialogueAfterLine: 0
    choices: []
    objectivesToActivate: []
  - LineID: Mean
    Speaker: Reed
    text: Uhm, okay...I'll make it quick then.
    lineTone: 2
    NPCGender: male
    NextLineID: Part I
    endDialogueAfterLine: 0
    choices: []
    objectivesToActivate: []
  - LineID: Part I
    Speaker: Reed
    text: As you know, Darry and I lived together. One day, I brought home a new
      TV only to find it broken on the floor the next day, with my car missing as
      well. I was furious. I waited all day for him to come back, so I could kick
      his ass...
    lineTone: 2
    NPCGender: male
    NextLineID: 
    endDialogueAfterLine: 0
    choices:
    - text: (Stay focused.)
      NextLineID: Part II
      moralityChange: 1
      direction: 0
      objectiveToActivate: 
    - text: (Doze off.)
      NextLineID: Part VI
      moralityChange: -1
      direction: 1
      objectiveToActivate: 
    objectivesToActivate: []
  - LineID: Part II
    Speaker: Reed
    text: ...Later on, Derry came back and I got on his case...it got nasty, almost
      physical, then I drove away. While I was driving, I noticed a receipt for a
      TV from earlier that day. I checked the trunk and realized Derry went and got
      a new TV.
    lineTone: 2
    NPCGender: male
    NextLineID: Part III
    endDialogueAfterLine: 0
    choices: []
    objectivesToActivate: []
  - LineID: Part IV
    Speaker: Reed
    text: The house was up in flames. The fire fighters did everything they could,
      and when I asked about Derry...I still remember the look on the paramedic's
      face.
    lineTone: 2
    NPCGender: male
    NextLineID: Part V
    endDialogueAfterLine: 0
    choices: []
    objectivesToActivate: []
  - LineID: Part V
    Speaker: Reed
    text: I really appreciate you listening. It means more than you think.
    lineTone: 1
    NPCGender: male
    NextLineID: Part VII
    endDialogueAfterLine: 0
    choices: []
    objectivesToActivate: []
  - LineID: Part VI
    Speaker: Reed
    text: Sorry, my emotional baggage is the last thing you'd care about.
    lineTone: 2
    NPCGender: male
    NextLineID: Part VII
    endDialogueAfterLine: 0
    choices: []
    objectivesToActivate: []
  - LineID: Part VII
    Speaker: Reed
    text: Sh*%, I completely forgot to clean up the leaves like I told Stevey I would.
      I'm a mess.
    lineTone: 2
    NPCGender: male
    NextLineID: Part VIII
    endDialogueAfterLine: 0
    choices: []
    objectivesToActivate: []
  - LineID: Part VIII
    Speaker: Reed
    text: I'm sorry to ask this of you Echo, but is there any chance you'll clean
      up the leaves? I'm sure Stevey will have something cool for you as a reward.
    lineTone: 2
    NPCGender: male
    NextLineID: 
    endDialogueAfterLine: 0
    choices:
    - text: Don't worry about it, go home.
      NextLineID: Part IX
      moralityChange: 1
      direction: 0
      objectiveToActivate: 
    - text: I'll do it, but you owe me.
      NextLineID: Part X
      moralityChange: -1
      direction: 1
      objectiveToActivate: 
    objectivesToActivate: []
  - LineID: Part IX
    Speaker: Reed
    text: You're a lifesaver, Echo! Grab a trash bag out of the shed and use that
      to grab the leaves, then toss the bag in the trash when you're done. Thanks
      again!
    lineTone: 1
    NPCGender: male
    NextLineID: 
    endDialogueAfterLine: 1
    choices: []
    objectivesToActivate:
    - stackLeaves
  - LineID: Part X
    Speaker: Reed
    text: I guess that's fair. Let me know what exactly that is next time I see you.
      You can grab a trash bag out of the shed to bag the leaves, then throw it in
      the dumpster after. Thanks for helping me.
    lineTone: 0
    NPCGender: male
    NextLineID: 
    endDialogueAfterLine: 1
    choices: []
    objectivesToActivate:
    - stackLeaves
